race.comment: EFFORTLESSLY (15) looks hard to beat. Ran an improved race last time when kept coming but found one better. Senior rider goes aboard now and looks suited out in trip. Expected to go close. MASMELO (16) made her debut in stakes class then was put away. Resumed over 1400m at Belmont and after drifting back wound up strongly for fourth. Has a wide gate to overcome so likely to be giving a start again but motoring home late. SAVVY RULER (8) started at big odds fresh and was safely held in what has been a hot form race. Fitter and this is more suitable. Can improve sharply. BUON AMICI (5) sat deep and was fair fresh. Much fitter for it and the extra trip is a plus. Pike goes aboard and should be running on hard. ROSENTREA (6) hasn't been far away and with the claim is nicely weighted. Another who will be running on.
